reviews.text: Came for the French onion soup stayed for everything else! The service was prompt and friendly shout out to Jackie who had to deal with me this evening! She was pleasant as could be and attended to every need with a smile. I would come hungry as the portions were large and I barely could get past the appetizer menu! If your within 30 minutes of driving I highly recommend coming by and have a bite or 3. The cocktails don‚Äôt disappoint either! Can‚Äôt wait to come back with the family!

This place is FANTASTIC!
The selection is great, the food is excellent and the service (both servers and bus) are some of the finest I‚Äôve ever encountered. Keep up the good work folks!!! Definitely be back.

The food was delicious! I had the veggie wrap with sweet potato fries and the pierogi appetizer both were great!The service was good, a little slow, and didn‚Äôt check on us. The atmosphere was very loud and we got sat right next to a table of about 15 people consisting of a girls (middle school age) softball team and some parents. I do have to say it was a Saturday afternoon, and the place was busy, so that is a great compliment to the food and restaurant. I would definitely go back when in the area again.

We visited for the first time on Friday 6/13.  We live in lower bucks and had never heard of this place I recently had seen a Tik Tok about their soup and many other dishes so we decided to try it out. It was me, my husband and 3 younger kids.  There was a little bit of wait but the staff advised us they had a happy hour and we could grab some drinks while we waited so we got 2 surfsides which were discounted.  When we sat, our waitress Jacqueline was amazing. We explained we had never been before and wanted to try everything as it all sounded so good.  She helped with some recommendations and everything was incredible!! We had the French Onion Soup, Spicy Queso Dip, and Onion Rings (with spicy ranch that was so good) as our starters.  For dinner we got the Southwest Burger, Philly cheesesteak and some kids meals.  My burger was huge and had a big pile of fried onion straws (I could honestly eat a basket of these as an appetizer) it was loaded with the toppings and cooked perfectly. The cheesesteak was also great!  Kids loved their meal.   The portions were all big and  at a great value for us.  We found a new spot we will be visiting often!  Shout out to whoever runs Tik Tok for you because it got us there and have told all our friends!

Food is always great.  Courtney makes the absolute best drinks behind the bar.  Appetizers are incredible.  The short rib pirogies and stuffed shrimp imperial are our favorite.  Can‚Äôt say enough good things about this place!
